# Implementation Plan: High-Performance Astro Portfolio

## Goal
Build a "supreme fast", elegant, and classy personal portfolio website for Ranil Mukesh using Astro.js. The design will follow a strict **pure black and white** aesthetic with neutral grays for depth, featuring ultra-smooth transitions and a mobile-responsive, spacious layout.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Aesthetic Specs**: Pure black (#000000) and white (#FFFFFF) with neutral grays (#F5F5F5, #1A1A1A) for subtle depth.
>
> **Top-Right Toggle**: The light/dark mode toggle will be fixed in the top-right corner for consistent access across all scroll positions.
>
> **Ultra-Smooth Transitions**: I will leverage Astro's `<ViewTransitions />` API combined with fine-tuned CSS cubic-bezier transitions for a premium, non-jarring feel.

## Proposed Changes

### Architecture & Design System
- **Framework**: Astro.js (Latest)
- **Styling**: Scoped Vanilla CSS + CSS Variables.
- **Color Palette**: 
  - Light: Primary White (#FFFFFF), Secondary Gray (#F5F5F5), Text Black (#000000).
  - Dark: Primary Black (#000000), Secondary Gray (#1A1A1A), Text White (#FFFFFF).
- **Layout**: Spacious with generous whitespace (80px+ section padding, clear readable line-height).
- **Transitions**: Global fade and slide animations using `view-transition-name` where applicable.

